SIMPLE: hug
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hug
<hw>Hug</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Hugged</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Hugging</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Prob. of Scand. origin; cf. Dan.
<ets>sidde paa huk</ets> to squat, Sw. <ets>huka sig</ets> to squat,
Icel. <ets>h<?/ka</ets>. Cf. <er>Huckster</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To cower; to crouch; to curl up.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Palsgrave.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To crowd together; to cuddle.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hug</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hug
<hw>Hug</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To press closely within
the arms; to clasp to the bosom; to embrace.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧And
<xex>huggen</xex> me in his arms.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To hold fast; to cling to; to cherish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We <qex>hug</qex> deformities if they bear our names.</q>
<rj><qau>Glanvill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To keep close to; <as>as, to
<ex>hug</ex> the land; to <ex>hug</ex> the wind.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To hug one's self</b></col>, <cd>to congratulate one's
self; to chuckle.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hug</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Hug
<hw>Hug</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A close embrace or clasping with the
arms, as in affection or in wrestling.</def>
<rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Huge</ent>⟦br⟧
